Use candidate edges as recall hints, not as mandatory output. Keep only article-grounded mainline relations.
For every retained edge, its source_quote must directly ground that exact from -> to relation. Use the Article as the primary edge signal, especially when the causal or inferential relation is expressed across adjacent clauses or sentences.
Favor recall for major adjacent/cross-sentence bridges when the Article span clearly states the economic transmission or forecast inference; omit only edges whose relation is not actually grounded.
Set relation kind to `inference` when a research clue, historical precedent, policy signal, legal feasibility point, or quantitative indicator is used to infer a future regime/outcome rather than mechanically cause it.
